<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1810,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,254,1810,1835]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="480" reason="1">General.</emphasis>
Body stout; legs quite thin; bright colors with mixed combination of blackish-steel blue, red, yellow, and sometimes orange. Body surface heavily pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[745,886,1846,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1970,1992]" captionTargetBox="[300,1293,195,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[300,1293,195,1948]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of both known color forms of male specimens of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Holotype; lighter color form. B. Paratype; darker color form. C. Thoracic view of the holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914513/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">Figs. 2A&amp;B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[898,934,1846,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1713,1735]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-126@5.[151,1436,193,1692]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Photographs of the known color form of an adult female specimen (paratype) of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Lateral view. B. Thoracic view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914515" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914515/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">3A</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[995,1012,1846,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[318,1274,193,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-58@6.[318,1274,193,1961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Photographs of known color forms of nymphal specimens of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Female; lighter color form. B. Female; darker color form. C. Male; darker color form." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914517/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">4</figureCitation>
). Extremely peculiar pronotum shape with raised, swollen, and smooth prozona, and extremely rugose metazona. Sulcus very deep, lateral carinae absent (
<figureCitation box="[159,257,1918,1943]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1970,1992]" captionTargetBox="[300,1293,195,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[300,1293,195,1948]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of both known color forms of male specimens of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Holotype; lighter color form. B. Paratype; darker color form. C. Thoracic view of the holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914513/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">Figs. 2C</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[316,351,1918,1943]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1713,1735]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-126@5.[151,1436,193,1692]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Photographs of the known color form of an adult female specimen (paratype) of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Lateral view. B. Thoracic view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914515" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914515/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">3B</figureCitation>
). Tegmina brachypterous and tectiform, widely oval, densely-reticulated, covering 3/4 of male and 3/5 of female abdomen; overlapping partially on dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[848,986,1954,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1970,1992]" captionTargetBox="[300,1293,195,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-60@4.[300,1293,195,1948]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of both known color forms of male specimens of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Holotype; lighter color form. B. Paratype; darker color form. C. Thoracic view of the holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914513/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">Figs. 2A&amp;B</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1040,1078,1954,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1713,1735]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-126@5.[151,1436,193,1692]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Photographs of the known color form of an adult female specimen (paratype) of Liladownsia fraile gen. nov. sp. nov.: A. Lateral view. B. Thoracic view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914515" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4914515/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
